### Diagram covers:
1. **DNS resolution** — browser → recursive resolver → root → TLD → authoritative NS → IP
2. **TCP/IP** — 3-way handshake (SYN / SYN-ACK / ACK) on port 443
3. **Firewall** — packet inspection, DDoS protection (Layer 3 & 7)
4. **HTTPS/TLS** — certificate validation, key exchange, AES-256 encrypted channel
5. **Load balancer** — round-robin, health checks, Anycast routing
6. **Web server** — HTTP/2 request parsing, static routing
7. **Application server** — business logic, dynamic HTML generation
8. **Database** — Spanner/Bigtable queries, Redis cache lookups
